<p class='talk-transcript__para'>
<data class='talk-transcript__para__time'>
15:59
</data>
<span class='talk-transcript__para__text'>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='948000' id='t-948000'>This kind of thinking drives economists crazy, and it should.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='952000' id='t-952000'>Because this 100 dollars that you save -- hello! --</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='956000' id='t-956000'>doesn't know where it came from.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='958000' id='t-958000'>It doesn't know what you saved it on.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='960000' id='t-960000'>When you go to buy groceries with it, it doesn't go,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='962000' id='t-962000'>I'm the money saved on the car stereo, or,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='965000' id='t-965000'>I'm the dumb money saved on the car. It's money.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='969000' id='t-969000'>And if a drive across town is worth 100 bucks, it's worth 100 bucks</span>
